<P ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="-1" COLOR="GREEN"><I>Rig Veda</I>, tr. by Ralph T.H. Griffith, [1896], at sacred-texts.com</FONT></P><HR></p>  <h3 align="center" align="center">HYMN CLXXXV. Aditi.</h3>  
<p>1. GREAT, unassailable must he the heavenly favour of Three Gods,<br> Varu&#7751;a, Mitra, Aryaman.<br> 2 O'er these, neither at home nor yet abroad or pathways that are Strange,<br> The evil-minded foe hath power<br> 3 Nor over him,. the man on whom the Sons of Aditi bestow Eternal light that he may live.</p>  
